How to add a new test suite?

Lets take the example of ViewLayout test suite.
+ Create ViewLayout.test.ts
+ Add license header
+ Add the root level describe:

    describe('ViewLayout', function() {

        // Write all tests inside this block.

    });

+ Write all test code inside the root level describe function block.

+ Pull in all the necessary typescript source code in ** sources.ts ** for which the tests are written.

    /// <reference path="../src/app/ViewLayout.ts" />
    /// <reference path="../src/app/ViewLayoutMultiPage.ts" />
    /// <reference path="../src/app/LayoutingService.ts" />

+ Finally add reference the test file ViewLayout.test.ts in ** main.ts **

    /// <reference path="./ViewLayout.test.ts" />


Now to run this newly created test suite, run from browser/ dir:

$ touch mocha_tests/main.ts && make build-tests && npm run test-single ViewLayout

